<h1>Working at NYGC</h1>

<p>The New York Grant Company is constantly looking for talented and enthusiastic people to join our team. The New York Grant Company is an EOE employer; we are committed to diversity. If you are interested in a career, please send a cover letter, resume and writing sample to <a href="mailto:ann@nygrants.com">ann@nygrants.com</a>. Or, if you prefer the old fashioned way, you can mail your application to:</p>
<p style="padding-left:20px;" >New York Grant Company<br />
Attn: Ann Kayman, CEO<br />
29 Broadway, Suite 2222<br />
New York, NY 10006<br /></p>

<h3>Salespersons</h3>
<p>NYGC seeks several commissioned salespeople in the field to attract new clients. Clients will include mid- to large- sized businesses, not-for-profits and educational institutions that may be eligible for economic incentives in the New York Metro Area. NYGC may advance reasonable work expenses, such as local travel, Internet access, cell phone related to sales calls, etc. Work from home is also fine with flexible hours. Prior sales experience very helpful. No degree required, but person must be able to learn and become conversant in economic development programs. Excellent oral and written communications and interpersonal skills a must! Successful salespeople will have opportunities to move to base pay plus commissions and benefits. Come join a great team and offer a much needed and valued service to the client community we serve!</p>

<h3>Freelance Grant Writers</h3>
<p>NYGC seeks one or more freelance grant writers to perform the following:</p>
<ol>
	<li>Interact with not-for-profit and business clients to prepare grant applications in the arts, sciences, community development, job training, workforce development, "green" projects and other fields.</li>
	<li>Research potential grant sources and write research reports to clients.</li>
	<li>Write grant applications, including letters of interest and full grant proposals, both electronic and traditional.</li>
	<li>Prepare grant packages and analyze underlying supporting documents. Prepare indices, charts, and budget spreadsheets to support grant applications.</li>
</ol>
<p>Hourly or per project fee based upon experience and qualifications. Bachelor's degree required. One to two years experience preferred. Must have excellent oral and written communication skills and client service skills. Previous grant writing or proposal writing or the equivalent experience a must. Help us serve our local not-for-profit community by getting them the grants they need to sustain themselves and the people and causes they serve! This is an excellent resume and contact builder.</p>

<h3>Junior Analysts</h3>
<p>NYGC seeks a full-time or part-time person to process applications for grants and incentives for the company's diverse clients. Must have excellent communications skills (oral and written) and outstanding client relations skills. Must know Excel, Word and Outlook. Knowledge of ACT! Or other project management programs very helpful. Prefer college degree and person with local knowledge about New York. Company will train employee in relevant incentives and grants. Willingness to work in a small office environment where everyone is always learning, lending a helpful hand, and engaging in teamwork--absolute musts!</p>
<p>Salary, benefits, and incentives (commissions/bonus) based upon experience and qualifications.</p>
</div>